getLevelZeroWords

public java.util.Vector getLevelZeroWords(java.lang.String user_name,
                                          java.lang.String test_type,
                                          Storage store)

This class seemed like a good place to Get a list of words with levels of a certain type at level 0.

These methods were originally in the WeeklyWordListAction.

It takes a bit of work to get a list of words at level zero and words that failed a test above level zero that contains no repeats.

Yes we could have made the level zero lists as hastables and done this possibly in one pass in one method, but we are leaving open the option of that in the future while currently using the lists in their natural habitats.

This is after all just a demostration application of how foreign language vocabulary can be learned with a thorough implemetation of the idea of intermittent re-inforcement.

See the notes for getNoRepeatsMissedWords1 to see how to make this list.

Get words that have been tested and found wanting.

This is controlled by settings in the users .option file in their folder.

Typically settings would be for only words at a level above 0 that have been failed recently.

getNoRepeatsMissedWords1

public java.util.Hashtable getNoRepeatsMissedWords1(java.lang.String type,
                                                    java.lang.String root_path,
                                                    java.lang.String user_name,
                                                    java.util.Hashtable user_opts,
                                                    java.util.Hashtable previous_missed_words,
                                                    java.util.Vector previous_words)

Third verse, same as the first, just a little be slimmer and a little bit worse.

No, seriously, to use this method, you have to first construct a Vector of concatenated level 0 words to exlcude missed words that are already in those lists.

This is done by first using the getLevelZeroWords method, usually to retrieve a list of words that have a level zero reading level.

Then we pass that list to the getFilteredLevelZeroWords with type writing to return a list of words at writing level zero that excludes words already in the first list.

Then we get to this method, where the first time thru we pass it type = reading, and the previous Vectors concatenated (done externally) list or reading and writing words at level 0, and blank Hastable of previous_missed_words because we dont have any yet.

Then we pass this method type=writing and the Hastable or missed words from the last time thru to creade a Hashtable that excludes words at level zero, and missed reading words.

It therefore takes a bit of work to get a list of words at level zero and words that failed a test above level zero that contains no repeats.

Yes we could have made the level zero lists as hastables and done this possibly in one pass in one method, but we are leaving open the option of that in the future while currently using the lists in their natural habitats.

This is after all just a demostration application of how foreign language vocabulary can be learned with a thorough implemetation of the idea of intermittent re-inforcement.
